Feature Plan: VenuesDetailsVC redesign with scroll blur and vertical controls (UIKit)

Objective
- Redesign `VenuesDetailsVC` based on `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/image1.png` direction while keeping all existing functions/flows unchanged.
- Keep rectangular movie media region.
- Add scroll-up blur progression over hero image/video.
- Reorder content: details text first, then vertically aligned action buttons.

Constraints
- UIKit-only implementation.
- Do not alter action method contracts or segue identifiers.
- Do not alter auth/header/payload contract behavior.
- Keep current data manager and payment/date/map flows intact.

Role ownership
- Primary iOS implementation: `@ios-dev`
- Contract regression checks: `@backend-dev`
- Manual flow verification: `@testing-engineer`

Target files
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesDetailsVC.swift`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesdetailsvc-redesign.prototype.html`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.venuesdetailsvc-redesign.specify`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.venuesdetailsvc-redesign.tasks`

High-level architecture
1. Hero media region
   - Keep top rectangular movie area (image/video).
   - Keep existing media pipeline with minimal structure changes.
2. Scroll container and blur bridge
   - Introduce/confirm scroll tracking callback.
   - Map upward scroll offset to blur intensity (0 -> max) over hero area.
   - Clamp values to avoid overdraw spikes.
3. Vertical content hierarchy
   - Place description/details text block first in content stack.
   - Place action buttons in vertical column below text.
   - Preserve original action handlers and labels.
4. Navigation and actions preservation
   - Keep `book`, `dates`, `map`, `movieDetail`, `selectCalendar`, `navigateBack` intact.
   - Keep existing popover behavior for dates/seats.
5. Stability/performance guardrails
   - Ensure one-time setup guards stay in place.
   - Avoid repeated player creation and duplicate subviews.

Interaction behavior
- Scroll up gradually blurs hero background and reveals a focused control region.
- Text panel remains ahead of button stack for readability and flow.
- Buttons stay vertically aligned with comfortable spacing.
- Existing user journeys remain unchanged.

Verification strategy
- Manual visual verify: rectangle hero, blur progression, text-before-buttons, vertical button stack.
- Manual flow verify: book/dates/map/movie detail/calendar/back all still work.
- Log verify: no new noisy layout observation loops introduced by redesign.
- Compile verify: no Swift errors in `VenuesDetailsVC.swift`.

Definition of done
- Speckit artifacts (`.specify`, `.plan`, `.tasks`, prototype) are complete and aligned.
- UIKit redesign direction approved from prototype review.
- Existing VenuesDetailsVC behavior preserved.

